               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240715-155-person1371">
                  MARY 
                  COUSINS
               <interp inst="t18240715-155-person1371" type="surname" value="COUSINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240715-155-person1371" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240715-155-person1371" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My husband's name is James. The prisoner came on Friday, the 14th of May, and took a furnished room in our house; there was a blanket, a carpet, and some flat irons let to her as part of the furniture; on the Monday after, I went into the room and missed the carpet, blanket and two flat irons; she came back about nine o'clock in the morning - and said she was going out ironing - I found the articles at Mr. Griffiths, the pawnbrokers.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240715-155-person1372">
                  JOHN 
                  GRIFFITHS
